cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IT

This paper proposes a neural network model for learning arbitrary noise distributions, which is relevant to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves optimization techniques, which are commonly used in neural networks and optimization theory (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the model, which relates to information theory (cs.IT).
